Polish Ruling Party’s Lead Falls While Opposition Party Advances

-- B y   D o r o t a   B a r t y z e l
-- 
2011-07-30T08:19:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-30/polish-ruling-party-s-lead-falls-while-opposition-party-advances.html
Support for  Poland ’s ruling party,
 Civic Platform , fell to 38 percent in July, down 2 percentage
points from June, according to a poll by the Warsaw-based
SMG/KRC agency for private television  TVN24 .  The largest opposition party, Law & Justice, was backed by
28 percent of Poles, 1 percentage point higher than the month
before, according to the July 29 survey of 1,000 adult Poles. No
margin of error was provided.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dorota Bartyzel in Warsaw at 
 dbartyzel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  